The paper deals with the Token Sliding problem, which is a graph theoretical problem related to independent sets. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The problem is also related to graph connectivity and chordal graphs, which suggests that it could be classified under the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Combinatorics (cs.CC) sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the complexity of the problem, which implies that it could also be classified under the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
